                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13003737" author="vidhyash" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2011 00:54:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have attached my patch to ensure completebulkload can be used even during table creation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, currently, the tool uses the default schema to create the table (just like load_table.rb did).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I got SocketTimeoutExceptions when I created a really large table: for now, I simply catch it and continue to sleep if the table isnt yet available. Any suggestions are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13003821" author="stack" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2011 05:59:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good V.  Usually we put space around the operators such as &apos;=&apos;.  Any chance of a comment in patch on what inferBoundaries is doing?  I&apos;m not sure I get it.  Any chance of a test?  You could make inferBoundaries static.  Would be easy to write a test for it then?  So, when this patch goes in, we should remove load_table.rb at same time?  Or better, turn it into a pointer to completeBulkLoad?  Good stuff V.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13007100" author="vidhyash" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 19:03:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The updated version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007103" author="vidhyash" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 19:05:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, load_table.rb should be removed (Havent included that in the patch). With this patch, completebulkload now works for uncreated tables too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007192" author="stack" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 21:12:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;V: Looks good.  Odd thing is your mixing of the test into the src. Usually we&apos;ll move this out to a class of its own.  I can add that on commit np.  Regards the question for reviewer, yes, first key would be &quot;&quot;, not &apos;a&apos;.  What do you do for first key when splitting?  Does it matter if it uses &apos;a&apos; or &quot;&quot; since its first key?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This code working for you V in your context?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can change load_table.rb too on commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007212" author="vidhyash" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 21:46:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The question should be rephrased as &lt;br/&gt;
Should the eventual boundary split be &apos;&apos;,a,m,r,u,&apos;&apos; or &apos;&apos;,m,r,u,&apos;&apos; ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current code will produce a key split of &apos;&apos;,a,m,r,u,&apos;&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was assuming you wanted a test code just for you guys to test if it works as intended: Do you want this test code also in the HBase source considering it is a test extremely local to a particular function? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007213" author="stack" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 21:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think you want ,m,r,u.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test should be out in a junit over in src/test, yes, even if extremely local.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good on you V.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007286" author="vidhyash" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 23:43:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find updated patch attached. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added the test to TestLoadIncrementalHFiles and it passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I have fixed the first boundary problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007611" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2011 18:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;V&apos;s patch plus clean up of loadtable.rb.  It now prints &quot;DISABLED!!!! Use completebulkload instead.  See tail of &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/bulk-loads.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/bulk-loads.html&lt;/a&gt;&quot; when invoked.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13007612" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2011 18:29:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied trunk and branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007614" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2011 18:30:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Made you a contributor V and assigned you this issue.  Thanks for the nice patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007634" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2011 19:15:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I removed from branch.  It was using an API not available in HFile.Reader out on branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007879" author="hudson" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 10:33:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1792 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1792/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1792/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13230551" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 15 Mar 2012 21:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doing a few edits to this jira:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it was committed to 0.92 (trunk back then), not 0.90.2&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the adding of the Exception on LoadIncrementalHFiles&apos;s constructor breaks the code that depends on it, so I marked it as an incompatible change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15017000" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:41:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
